'''Dōmo arigatō''' is a [[Japan|Japanese]] expression that translates to "Thank you." Knowledge of the expression was popularized in the Western world at least in part by the song [[Mr. Roboto]] which features the line "''Dōmo arigatō'', Mr. Roboto."

The line has been used as a pop culture reference a number of times, including in the film '[[Austin Powers in Goldmember]]', the song "The King Of Bedside Manor" by the [[Barenaked Ladies]], The song "[[Mr.Roboto]]" by [[Styx]], and cartoons [[Futurama]] and [[The Simpsons]].

<br>The line has also been included in the famous song "Mr. Roboto" by the band Styx.


